ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Semantic Fluency: Name as many animals / living creatures as you can in one minute(Raw Score)
Semantic Fluency: Name as many animals / living creatures as you can in one minute(Pass/Fail)
Notes: 0=Pass; 1=Fail; Fail if Semantic Fluency raw score is 15 or less

ElementDescription: Phonemic Fluency: Name as many words as you can in one minute that start with the letter ''F''. Do not use names of people or places(Raw Score)
Phonemic Fluency: Name as many words as you can in one minute that start with the letter''F''. Do not use names of people or places(Pass/Fail)
Notes: 0=Pass; 1=Fail; Fail if Phonemic Fluency raw score is 8 or less

ElementDescription: Category Switching: Name a vegetable and then a type of profession or job; and then another vegetable and another profession; and so on. Name as many words as you can in one minute(Raw Score)
Notes: Total number of correct alternating words

ElementDescription: Category Switching: Name a vegetable and then a type of profession or job; and then another vegetable and another profession; and so on. Name as many words as you can in one minute(Pass/Fail)
Notes: 0=Pass; 1=Fail; Fail if Category Switching Raw Score is 10 or less

ElementDescription: Digit Span Forward: Repeat the following numbers. 4;8;7;0(Read aloud at a rate of 1 per second. Start with 4;8;7;0 and administer previous items if subject fails to repeat 4;8;7;0).
Digit Span Forward: Repeat the following numbers. 5;9(Read aloud at a rate of 1 per second. Start with 4;8;7;0 and administer previous items if subject fails to repeat 4;8;7;0).
Digit Span Forward: Repeat the following numbers. 2;1;3(Read aloud at a rate of 1 per second. Start with 4;8;7;0 and administer previous items if subject fails to repeat 4;8;7;0).
Digit Span Forward: Repeat the following numbers. 1;6;9;2;5(Read aloud at a rate of 1 per second. Start with 4;8;7;0 and administer previous items if subject fails to repeat 4;8;7;0).
Digit Span Forward: Repeat the following numbers. 3;0;1;2;6;3(Read aloud at a rate of 1 per second. Start with 4;8;7;0 and administer previous items if subject fails to repeat 4;8;7;0).
Digit Span Forward: Repeat the following numbers. 7;3;1;9;8;4;6(Read aloud at a rate of 1 per second. Start with 4;8;7;0 and administer previous items if subject fails to repeat 4;8;7;0).
Digit Span Forward: Repeat the following numbers. 2;0;5;6;9;7;3;8(Read aloud at a rate of 1 per second. Start with 4;8;7;0 and administer previous items if subject fails to repeat 4;8;7;0).
Digit Span Forward: Raw Score
Notes: Maximum string of numbers correctly repeated

ElementDescription: Digit Span Forward: Pass/Fail
Notes: 0=Pass; 1=Fail; Fail if Digit Span Forward Raw score 5 or less

ElementDescription: Digit Span Backward: Repeat the following numbers backwards (in reverse order) 6;1
Digit Span Backward: Repeat the following numbers backwards (in reverse order) 3;8;2
Digit Span Backward: Repeat the following numbers backwards (in reverse order) 4;7;0;9
Digit Span Backward: Repeat the following numbers backwards (in reverse order) 6;5;2;8;1
Digit Span Backward: Repeat the following numbers backwards (in reverse order) 5;9;0;3;7;4
Digit Span Backward: Raw Score
Notes: Maximum string of numbers correctly repeated. Fail if score 4 or less. Inability to reverse 2 digits scores 0

ElementDescription: Digit Span Backward: Pass/Fail
Cube(Draw): Draw a cube(a six-sided box); make it transparent or see-through.
Notes: Score = 15 points if 12 lines present and diagram is 3-dimensional. If 12 lines not present or the diagram is not 3 dimensional; administer "CUBE (COPY)".

ElementDescription: Cube(Copy): Copy the cube shown on PAGE 2
Notes: Score = 12 points; 1 for each line. Deduct 1 point if not 3-D; 1 point for each line not drawn; 1 point for each additional line >12.

ElementDescription: Cube: Pass/Fail
Verbal Recall: Spontaneous Recall(Flower)
Verbal Recall: Spontaneous Recall(Robert)
Verbal Recall: Spontaneous Recall(Courage)
Verbal Recall: Spontaneous Recall(Speak)
Verbal Recall: Spontaneous Recall(Yellow)
Verbal Recall: Recall with category cue(Flower)
Verbal Recall: Recall with category cue(Robert)
Verbal Recall: Recall with category cue(Courage)
Verbal Recall: Recall with category cue(Speak)
Verbal Recall: Recall with category cue(Yellow)
Verbal Recall: Recall with multiple choice(Flower)
Verbal Recall: Recall with multiple choice(Robert)
Verbal Recall: Recall with multiple choice(Courage)
Verbal Recall: Recall with multiple choice(Speak)
Verbal Recall: Recall with multiple choice(Yellow)
Verbal Recall: Raw Score
Notes: Spontaneous = 3 points per word; category = 2 points ; multiple choice = 1 point. Score = total points. Inability to recall more than 1 word from multiple choice raises concern for cerebral involvement.

ElementDescription: Verbal Recall: Pass/Fail
Similarities: How are the following words alike; what is the same about them?(Nose/Ear)
Similarities: How are the following words alike; what is the same about them?(Sheep/Elephant)
Similarities: How are the following words alike; what is the same about them?(Lake/River)
Similarities: How are the following words alike; what is the same about them?(Airplane/Motorcycle)
Similarities: Raw Score
Notes: Correct answer (conceptual) = 2 points; partial answer (concrete) = 1 point; incorrect answer / no answer = 0 points. Score = total points.

ElementDescription: Similarities: Pass/Fail
Go No-Go: When I tap the table once; raise your finger then put it back down again. When I tap the table twice; don't do anything.
Notes: 2 points for no errors; 1 point for one error; 0 points for two or more errors. Score = total points. Fail if Score 1 or less.

ElementDescription: Go No-Go: Pass; Fail
Affect: Difficulty with focusing attention or mental flexibility
Affect: Emotionally labile; incongruous emotions; appears hopeless or depressed
Affect: Shows easy sensory overload or avoidant behaviors
Affect: Expresses illogical thoughts or paranoia
Affect: Lacks empathy; is apathetic; or has blunted affect
Affect: Angry or aggressive; irritable; oppositional; difficulty with social cues and social boundaries
Affect: Total Work
Notes: Score 6 points if none are present. Subtract 1 for each item present. Fail if Score 4 or less.

ElementDescription: Affect: Pass/Fail
CCAS: Raw Total Score
CCAS: Total Failed Tests
Notes: 1 failed test=CCAS possible; 2 or more failed tests=CCAS probable

ElementDescription: Visit name
Notes: e.g., Baseline, 6-Month Follow Up, Year 2, Daily
